# Local notes only. Production secrets via:
#   npx wrangler secret put …
#
# Auth MVP: magic-link tokens live in D1; verify URL is returned in API
# response until an email provider is wired (Resend / Email Workers / etc.).
#
# Local stack (two processes — not one command with +):
#   Terminal A: npm run dev:api    # Worker + D1 + R2 on :8787
#   Terminal B: npm run dev        # Astro; /api and /media proxied to :8787
# Or one shot:  npm run dev:all
#
# R2: wrangler.toml binds MEDIA → dimela-mx-media.
# Local wrangler simulates the bucket. For remote deploy, enable R2 in the
# Cloudflare Dashboard, then:
#   npx wrangler r2 bucket create dimela-mx-media
#
# Demo login emails (seeded — see shared/demoAccounts.js + db/seed-auth.sql):
#   Members: romina@tortilla.studio, demo.{cristobal,miguel,cecilia,antonio,giovanni,mara,sandra}@dimela.mx
#   Admin:   hola@dimela.mx
#
# Beta one-click login (no email): /entrar/
#   Staging: BETA_LOGIN=true in wrangler.toml [vars] (see docs/beta-launch.md).
#   Optional shared key:
#     npx wrangler secret put BETA_LOGIN_SECRET
#   With secret: https://YOUR_HOST/entrar/?key=YOUR_SECRET
#   Buttons hit GET /api/auth/beta?demo=<key> (romina, cristobal, miguel, …, admin)
#   At public launch: follow docs/beta-launch.md checklist.
#
# Media uploads need the Worker (:8787 or deploy), not Astro alone.
# After deploy, run: npm run db:migrate:media:remote
#
# Later: AUTH_SECRET, Stripe keys, email OTP provider, etc.
